		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />That list is wrong about both mario 2 and 3.  They have pretty much the same setup and they both have wram.  
<br />
<br />As said earlier, learning what boards have wram and then using the "pretty comprehensive document" is probably the best way to make a list. I'm too lazy to make you a boards with wram list (much less a games with wram list), but you can figure most of them out from kevtris's mapper database:
<br />
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.tripoint.org/kevtris/mappers/mappers.html">http://www.tripoint.org/kevtris/mappers/mappers.html</a><!-- m -->

		

